CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 9, 1950, pg. 17 reads: "Shut-Ins Remembered at Leech Farm - More than 450 patients were recently made happy when representatives from the Young People's Department of the Women's Missionary Society made, and presented to them, favors.  The group has been distributing the tokens of good will for four years...Lower right: Young man gets gift from pretty girl.  Pictured are Miss Deloris White, Mrs. Mabel Little, Miss June Hardaway, Harrison Dorsey, and Miss Annette Holmes, telephone operator. -Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pictured are members of the Young People's Department of the Women's Missionary Society, left to right; Deloris White, Mabel Little, and June Hardaway, presenting gift to Harrison Dorsey, with telephone operator Annette Holmes, standing in interior at Leech Farm
